<a name="para"></a>
<table bgcolor="YELLOW">
<tbody><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="10">
<tbody><tr><th>What does "paraphyletic" mean?</th></tr>
<tr><td>A phylum is a group of animals.  "Para" means "next to" or "along side of".

So, paraphyletic means "a parallel group of animals."

The problem, for evolutionists, with the whale phylum and the hippo phylum being parallel is that they are <b>too</b> similar.

They are so similar, that they should be one phylum. Which, to them, implies common ancestry.

</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</td>
